  • Engine
    • Contains functions for manipulating core time card objects
    • Clock
      • inState
        • Create the object 'clock state' which is clocked in.
        • {Object<clockState>} {clockState: {in: <Date>}}
        • {Date} time The time when the person clocks in.
      • outState
        • The object 'clock state' which is clocked out.
      • defaultClockInfo
        • The object 'clock information' which is clocked out.
      • isClockedIn
        • Determines if clock state is clocked in or out.
        • {Boolean} True when clocked in otherwise false
        • {Object<clockInfo>} clockInfo The current state of the clock.
      • in
        • Clock in item.
        • {Object<clockInfo>} New information on the clock and hours status.
        • {Object<clockInfo>} clockInfo Information on the clock status.
        • {Date} clockInTime Time at which the person clocks in.
      • out
        • Clock out item.
        • {Object<clockInfo>} New information on the clock and hours status.
        • {Object<clockInfo>} clockInfo Information on the clock status.
        • {Date} clockOutTime Time at which the person clocks out.
      • toggle
        • Toggles the time by updating the hours during the day and reflecting the correct clock state.
        • {Object<clockInfo>} The new clock information after added time and clock state change.
        • {Object<clockInfo>} clockInfo The clock information.
        • {Date} dateTime The time when the clock was toggled.
        • isClockedIn
          • true
            • out
          • false
            • in
      • addTime
        Not implemented.
        • Adds additional time to singleDay object starting at the beginning of the day (or provided start time) onwards.
        • singleDay
        • singleDay array of doubles
        • additionalTime double
        • (startTime)
  • Utilities
    • Contains useful functions for general use.
    • stringSize
      • Takes an object and returns a string of specified length or less, trimmed.
      • {String} New string which has been trimmed and resized.
      • {String} string String to clean and resize.
      • {Number} size Integer to resize string to.
    • isWholeNumber
      • Takes a number and determines if it is a whole number.
      • {Boolean} True if whole number otherwise false.
      • {Number} number Number to test.
    • isBetween
      • Takes a number and determines if it is equal to or inbetween two other numbers.
      • {Boolean} True if between upper & lower bounds, otherwise false.
      • {Number} lower Lower bound to test.
      • {Number} upper Upper bound to test.
      • {Number} value Number to test.
    • areUnique
      • Determine if items in object are unique.
      • {Boolean} True if unique, otherwise false.
      • {Array<Object>} objects Objects to test if they are unique.
      • {String} property Property name of object to test against.
    • toFlatArray
      • Converts to array then flattens results.
      • {Array<Object>} Flattened array of objects.
      • {Object} object Object to put in flattened array.
    • complement
      • Takes complement of a function.
      • {function(*):Boolean} Function which returns the opposite of the original value.
      • {function(*):Boolean} predicate Function which returns a boolean.
    • addRollingArray
      • Adds a fraction value to array between two values.
      • {Array<Number>} a new array with added values.
      • {Array<Number>} array Original array values.
      • {Number} start Start index to begin can be fraction.
      • {Number} end End index to begin, can be be fraction.
      • {Number} fraction Value to add to array index, if at end or beginning will take the fraction of the value.
  • Core Objects
    • Contains core objects relating to the time card.
    • k
      • Constants
      • jobId
      • singleDay
      • in
      • out
      • state
      • day
      • jobList
    • Utils
      • Utilities specifically used with the Core objects.
      • validateJobId
        • Validates the job ID as a whole number.
      • validateSingleDay
        • Validates a single day as a float array of length 24 with numbers between -1 and 1.
      • validateDate
        • Validates the date as a real date.
      • validateClockState
        • Validates that input is an object 'in' or 'out'.
      • validateClockInfo
        • Validates that input contains the singleDay and clockState objects.
      • validateJobInfo
        • Validates that the input contains the clockInfo and jobId objects.
      • validateDay
        • Validates that the input contains the objects date and list of jobInfo. Also, validates that the list of jobInfo objects have unique job IDs.
    • Objects
      • Job
        • Represents an item for tracking time.
        • {id: Whole Number}
          • Unique.
      • SingleDay
        • Object which represents a single days time.
        • [0 .. 23]
        • Must be <= 1
        • Must be >= -1
        • Array values are doubles
      • In
        • Object representing the clocked in state.
        • {time: DateTime}
      • Out
        • Object representing clocked out state.
        • Empty {}
      • ClockState
        • Object which represents the toggle state of the job.
        • Object `In` when clocked in.
        • Object `Out` when clocked out.
      • ClockInfo
        • Contains objects ClockState and SingleDay.
      • JobInfo
        • Contains objects ClockInfo and Job
      • Day
        • Contains a list of JobInfo objects and the single date which they occurred on.
        • Date of JobInfo list
        • [JobInfo]
        • Job must have unique id
    • createJobId
      • Wraps integer (job ID) in an object with name 'jobId'.
      • id
      • {jobId: <value>}
    • createSingleDay
      • Creates an object which represents single days time in an array representing each hour of the day.
      • dayArray
      • {singleDay: Array<float:24>}
    • createIn
      • Creates an object representing the clock state of 'in' with its associated time.
      • dateTime
      • {in: <Date>}
    • createOut
      • Creates an object representing the clock state 'out'.
    • createClockState
      • Creates an object representing the clock state with values of 'in' or 'out'.
      • inOut
      • {clockState: <in|out>}
    • createClockInfo
      • Creates an object representing the information dealing with time, i.e., the clock state and hours worked.
      • singleDay
      • clockState
      • {singleDay: <Array<float>>, clockState: <in|out>}
    • createJobInfo
      • Aggregates clock information data with job ID.
      • clockInfo
      • jobId
      • {jobId: <value>, singleDay: <Array<float>>, clockState: <in|out>}
    • createDay
      • Aggregates list of job information with the date of the day associated with the list of job information.
      • date
        • Date associated with list of job information.
      • jobInfos
      • {day: <Date>, jobList: [jobInfo]}
  • Settings
    • Contains objects representing settings for the time card.
    • Job
      • Represents an item for tracking time.
      • {id: Whole Number}
        • Unique.
      • {active: Boolean}
      • {name: String}
        • 0 < name characters.
        • Unique.
    • Jobs
      • List of Job objects.
      • Unique
    • buttonColors
      • Colors of clocked out/in buttons
